The White House has announced a $50 million support package for Ukraine, aimed at helping the country establish security, pursue democratic elections and constitutional reform, revive its economy, and ensure transparent and accountable government institutions. The package includes support for elections and constitutional reform, economic assistance, energy security, rule of law and anti-corruption measures, people-to-people ties, and security assistance. The United States is committed to helping Ukraine determine its own future without intimidation or coercion from outside forces.